output.crosstab_text:
Among those who graduated ten years previously from first degree courses in Physics and astronomy and who were working during the 2021-22 tax year, Professional, scientific and technical activities was the most common industry for White and Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates, Education and Professional, scientific and technical activities were the most common industries for Black / African / Caribbean / Black British ethnicity graduates, and Education was the most common industry for Mixed / Multiple ethnic groups, Other ethnic group and Unknown ethnicity graduates.The industry with the largest range in proportions was Education, where Other ethnic group ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion.

The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Professional, scientific and technical activities, where Mixed / Multiple ethnic groups ethnicity graduates had the highest median earnings (£65,700) and White ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£55,800). The group with the highest earnings was Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates who worked in the Financial and insurance activities industry (median earnings of £79,600).
